
Overview of noun idealization

The noun idealization has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                   
1. (1) idealization, idealisation, glorification -- (a portrayal of something as ideal; "the idealization of rural life was very misleading")
2. idealization, idealisation -- ((psychiatry) a defense mechanism that splits something you are ambivalent about into two representations--one good and one bad)
3. idealization, idealisation -- (something that exists only as an idea)
